      • setSymlinkTarget

        public FilesTypes.FileAttributesInfo.Builder setSymlinkTarget(java.lang.String symlinkTarget)
        The target for the file if it's a symbolic link. This is currently only set for Posix guest operating systems, but may be supported in the future on Windows guest operating systems that support symbolic links. This property was added in vSphere API 7.0.2.0. Set if the file is a symbolic link.
        Parameters:
        symlinkTarget - New value for the property.

      • setWinAttributes

        public FilesTypes.FileAttributesInfo.Builder setWinAttributes(FilesTypes.WindowsFileAttributesInfo winAttributes)
        Windows-specific file information. This property was added in vSphere API 7.0.2.0. This property is optional and it is only relevant when the value of getFilesystemFamily() is FilesTypes.FilesystemFamily.WINDOWS.
        Parameters:
        winAttributes - New value for the property.

      • setPosixAttributes

        public FilesTypes.FileAttributesInfo.Builder setPosixAttributes(FilesTypes.PosixFileAttributesInfo posixAttributes)
        Posix-specific file information. This property was added in vSphere API 7.0.2.0. This property is optional and it is only relevant when the value of getFilesystemFamily() is FilesTypes.FilesystemFamily.POSIX.
        Parameters:
        posixAttributes - New value for the property.
